Hi there,

My team just recently got our hands on some Kraken X60’s and are looking into using them into the next season. This brings on where to start when getting them running. I have been though tons of different sites looking for if there is some form of client or application that can be used to get them running without code (for testing purposes.) I am also curious if there is somewhere else we should start first.

Any help is appreciated!

Thanks! - Katie FRC 2640

You can use CTRE’s application (called Phoenix Tuner X) in order to run Kraken manually. This is the docs for this application:

Phoenix 6

Phoenix Tuner X

What is Phoenix Tuner X?: Phoenix Tuner X is the companion application allowing you to update, configure, analyze, and control your devices. Phoenix Tuner X can be installed from the Microsoft Stor...
